Python Data Types - Definition & Explanation
In Python, a data type defines what kind of value a variable can store. Each variable in Python has a specific data type, which determines how the data is stored, manipulated, and used in operations.

Main Categories of Data Types in Python
Python has six main categories of data types:

Category	Data Types	Example
1. Numeric	int, float, complex	10, 3.14, 5+2j
2. Sequence	str, list, tuple, range	"hello", [1,2,3], (4,5,6), range(5)
3. Set	set, frozenset	{1, 2, 3}, frozenset({4,5,6})
4. Mapping	dict (dictionary)	{"name": "Ali", "age": 25}
5. Boolean	bool	True, False
6. Binary	bytes, bytearray, memoryview	b'hello', bytearray(5), memoryview(bytes(5))

